Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, low total CO₂, and significant proteinuria with glucosuria, low urine specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal). These findings suggest impaired renal function, possibly chronic kidney disease with tubular dysfunction. No evidence of urinary tract infection is present. Further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
